# Factory Council .gitignore

# Session logs may contain sensitive business context:
# - Financial details (runway, burn rate, specific numbers)
# - Strategic decisions not yet public
# - Personnel discussions
# - Customer-specific information
#
# DECISION FOR THE OPERATOR: Do you want to commit session logs to git?
#
# Option A: Keep logs in git (default — nothing below is uncommented)
#   Advantage: Full history, shareable, version-controlled
#   Risk: If this repo is public or shared, logs expose business context
#
# Option B: Gitignore session logs (uncomment the line below)
#   Advantage: Sensitive context stays local
#   Risk: No backup in git, not shareable via repo
#
# Uncomment to gitignore session logs:
# logs/*.md

# Always keep the template and directory structure
!logs/session-log-template.md
!logs/handoffs/.gitkeep
!logs/debates/.gitkeep
